62.6	Gary_Becker	Gary Becker	Gary Stanley Becker (born December 2, 1930) is an American economist. He is a professor of economics and sociology at the University of Chicago and a professor at the Booth School of Business. He was awarded the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences in 1992 and received the United States Presidential Medal of Freedom in 2007. He is currently a Rose-Marie and Jack R. Anderson senior fellow at Stanford University's Hoover Institution.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/GaryBecker-May24-2008.jpg/200px-GaryBecker-May24-2008.jpg
